----------------------------------------
0. What is HPCToolkit
----------------------------------------

HPCToolkit is an open-source suite of performance analysis tools.  It
consists of components for measuring the performance of
fully-optimized executables generated by vendor compilers, analyzing
application binaries to correlate measurements with program structure,
and novel analysis techniques for pinpointing performance bottlenecks
in parallel programs.

Its WWW page is http://hpctoolkit.org.

=============================================================================

----------------------------------------
1. Obtaining and Installing HPCToolkit
----------------------------------------

Source tarballs may be downloaded from:
  https://outreach.scidac.gov/projects/hpctoolkit

Alternatively, one may obtain a snapshot of the latest subversion
source tree.

In either case, see README.Install for directions on building and
installing HPCToolkit and its prerequisites.

